This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the deployment of middleboxes across geographically distributed data centers. It could also belong to the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it discusses the deployment of middleboxes across a distributed infrastructure. Additionally, it could belong to the sub-category of Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed) as it deals with the replication of state objects across a distributed infrastructure. It could also belong to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it discusses the performance and scalability of the system. Finally, it could belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with the security implications of remote state accesses.
